Source: egachine
Section: games
Priority: optional
Maintainer: Jens Thiele <karme@berlios.de>
Build-Depends: debhelper (>> 3.0.0), libsdl1.2-dev, libsdl-image1.2-dev, gcj, libgl-dev, libglu-dev
Standards-Version: 3.5.2

Package: egachine
Architecture: any
Depends: egachine-data, ${shlibs:Depends}
Description: a simple networked game engine
 EGachine (ECMA Script/Javascript Game machine) is a simple 
 networked game engine mainly intended but not limited to
 2D multi-player (networked) games. It should get
 beginners started with game programing and let you write 
 multi-player networked games quickly.
 For the advanced programmer OpenGL language bindings are
 included.
 .
 This package contains the executables.
 .
  Homepage: http://egachine.berlios.de
 
Package: egachine-data
Architecture: all
Depends: 
Description: egachine class library
 EGachine (ECMA Script/Javascript Game machine) is a simple 
 networked game engine mainly intended but not limited to
 2D multi-player (networked) games. It should get
 beginners started with game programing and let you write 
 multi-player networked games quickly.
 For the advanced programmer OpenGL language bindings are
 included.
 .
 This package contains scripts and data.
 .
  Homepage: http://egachine.berlios.de


